    <stitle>MULTI-LINK FRONT AIR SUSPENSION - REMOVE AND INSTALL PROCEDURES - TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transverse Torque Rod - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0301515" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301515.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Axle Mount Bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOCKNUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. AXLE MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>It is recommended the vehicle be unloaded prior to performing this procedure. Vehicle must be
                        at approximate air spring height.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the locknut from the axle mount bracket and transverse torque rod.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the transverse torque rod from the axle mount bracket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0301516" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301516.webp" type="webp" scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Transverse Torque Rod</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TRANSVERSE TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TRANSVERSE CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. THROUGH ROD ENDS</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. NUTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two bolts and nuts from the transverse torque rod and transverse crossmember.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the transverse torque rod from the transverse crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Transverse Torque Rod - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the transverse torque rod on the transverse crossmember.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure the transverse torque rod to the transverse crossmember with two bolts and nuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301516">Figure 120, Items 1, 3, and 5</hotlnk>). Torque bolts to 195 to 240 lbf-ft
                    (265 to 325 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the locknut on the axle mount bracket and transverse torque rod (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301515">Figure 19</hotlnk>). Torque locknut to 225 lbf-ft (305 N&#8226;m). Tap the
                    end of the transverse torque rod with a soft-faced mallet and re-torque locknut to 225 lbf-ft (305 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
